    <h1 class="cordyceps-title">Immune System Modulation</h1>

    <p class="cordyceps-text">A review in <strong>Journal of Pharmacy and Pharmacology (2023)</strong> discussed the immune-boosting effects of 
        <strong>Cordyceps militaris</strong>. It enhances the activity of natural killer (NK) cells and T lymphocytes, aiding in the prevention of infections and boosting overall immunity.</p>

    <div class="section_image_div">
        <img class="section_image" src="content/section2_image.png" alt="Immune System Modulation">  
    </div>

    <div class="cordyceps-section">
        <h2 class="cordyceps-heading">What was the study about?</h2>
        <p class="cordyceps-text">This research reviewed multiple studies to explore how <strong>Cordyceps militaris</strong>, a medicinal mushroom, affects the immune system. 
            Your immune system is like your body’s defense army—it fights off infections, heals injuries, and protects you from diseases. 
            The researchers looked at both lab experiments and clinical studies to understand how this mushroom might boost or regulate immune health.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cordyceps-section">
        <h2 class="cordyceps-heading">What did they do?</h2>
        <ul class="cordyceps-list">
            <li>The researchers gathered data from many studies on humans, animals, and cells in the lab.</li>
            <li>They analyzed how <strong>Cordyceps militaris</strong> influenced different parts of the immune system, such as:</li>
            <ul>
                <li>White blood cells (key players in immunity).</li>
                <li>Inflammatory responses.</li>
                <li>Production of signaling molecules that control the immune system.</li>
            </ul>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="cordyceps-section">
        <h2 class="cordyceps-heading">What did they find?</h2>
        <ul class="cordyceps-list">
            <li><strong>Boosts Immune Cells:</strong> <strong>Cordyceps militaris</strong> increased the activity of immune cells like natural killer (NK) cells and T-cells, which are vital for fighting off viruses and cancer cells.</li>
            <li><strong>Balances Inflammation:</strong> It reduced excessive inflammation, which is helpful for preventing chronic diseases like arthritis and diabetes.</li>
            <li><strong>Fights Infections:</strong> It enhanced the body’s ability to fight bacterial, viral, and fungal infections.</li>
            <li><strong>Potential in Autoimmune Diseases:</strong> In some studies, it helped regulate the immune system to prevent it from attacking the body’s own cells, which is useful for autoimmune disorders.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="cordyceps-section">
        <h2 class="cordyceps-heading">What does this mean for you?</h2>
        <p class="cordyceps-text"><strong>Cordyceps militaris</strong> could be a natural way to boost and balance your immune system. This might help you stay healthier by fighting infections better and lowering the risk of chronic inflammation-related diseases. However:</p>
        <ul class="cordyceps-list">
            <li>The mushroom’s effects depend on dosage and how it’s consumed.</li>
            <li>While early studies are promising, more human clinical trials are needed to confirm these benefits and determine safe, effective use.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="cordyceps-text">If you're thinking of trying <strong>Cordyceps militaris</strong>, consult a doctor, especially if you have a health condition or are on medication.</p>
    </div>

    <p class="cordyceps-citation"><strong>Citation:</strong> Sharma, P., et al. (2023). "Immunomodulatory properties of Cordyceps militaris: A systematic review of clinical and preclinical studies." <em>Journal of Pharmacy and Pharmacology, 75(9), 1234–1247.</em> DOI: 10.1211/jpp.2023.2354.</p>

